    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix checksum calculation in OPT probe module\n\n### Summary\nThe checksum function in the OPT probe module was not correctly handling odd-length data and had incomplete carry propagation, leading to incorrect IP header checksums. This caused malformed packets to be generated for PCAP output.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/UTIL/OPT/probe.c`: Fixed the `checksum()` function to properly handle odd-length data and improved carry propagation. Also fixed IP header checksum calculation by zeroing the checksum field before computation.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running OAI with PCAP tracing enabled, IP packets in the capture would have incorrect checksums, causing Wireshark to flag them as malformed. This was particularly noticeable with odd-length IP payloads where the last byte was not being included in the checksum calculation.\n\nThe issue can be observed by enabling OPT tracing and examining the generated PCAP files - IP header checksums will be incorrect, especially for packets with odd byte counts in their payload.\n\n"
}